  "text": "All the patients were advised to contact their physician immediately if they became sick, and particularly if they developed mouth ulcers or febrile illnesses. When severe neutropenia (absolute neutrophil count 1 0 x 109/1) developed, patients underwent prompt sternal bone marrow examination including Colony Forming Unit assay by a diffusion chamber technique [CITATION_1] .",
